arStrings.szText: The victims of my brother Baal. He laid waste to the barbarian lands long before your time. I wish I could have seen it with my own eyes...

A little wistful for the last sentence. Context for Wolphisto's lines: he is talking about barbarians who were killed by Baal in a previous Diablo game. They have appeared in Mephisto's realm, but they shouldn't be there.
I had no part in it, though. Elias has upset the balance at the Temple of the Primes, and those shades of the past belong in Baalâ€™s domain, not mine. But I do welcome their hatred.
